author: Inside Edition
description: Cardi B emerged from a Los Angeles courtroom victorious, cleared of assaulting a security guard. Many are talking about how the rapper had the jury in the palm of her hands from the very start. From her comedic facial expressions to her funny testimony, she charmed the courtroom. In a post trial news conference, Cardi was asked about her various hair-dos throughout the trial. After her not guilty verdict, Cardi was benevolent toward the security guard.
title: Cardi B Being Praised for Lessons in How to Win Over Jury From Stand

author: Inside Edition
description: An 8-year-old girl is in the hospital after a shark chomped down on her leg. Harper Ochoa and her mom Christa were enjoying a family beach vacation in Galveston, Texas. The family says they spend every summer at the Galveston beach and nothing like this has never happened. The brave youngster tells Inside Edition's Steven Fabian the shark bite "felt like a really big scratch … Like the most biggest scratch in existence."
title: 8-Year-Old in Hospital After Shark Bites Her Leg

author: Inside Edition
description: An image of accused killer Luigi Mangione, or someone who looks like him, on the clothing website Shein is causing many people to scratch their heads. Is it really him in the photo, or is it a case of AI? Mangione is awaiting trial for allegedly assassinating United Healthcare executive Brian Thompson last December in Manhattan. In a statement, Shein said the image "was provided by a third-party vendor and was removed immediately.” The company says it is conducting an investigation.
title: Is That Luigi Mangione Modeling for Shein?

author: Inside Edition
description: University of Kentucky senior Laken Snelling has been accused of hiding her dead newborn. Police say they went to Snelling's home after getting a report of a dead infant being found in a closet. They say they discovered the baby wrapped in a towel in a black trash bag. The 21-year-old allegedly "admitted to giving birth" and "concealing the birth." It is not clear how the baby died or who called the police. Snelling pleaded not guilty to abusing a corpse and tampering with evidence.
title: University Cheerleader Accused of Hiding Dead Infant in Closet

author: Inside Edition
description: Dozens of Jeffrey Epstein victims spoke out at a gathering in the nation's capital calling on the Justice Department to release the Epstein files. Marjorie Taylor Greene came together with Democrats to support legislation to get all the Epstein files released. Another strong Trump supporter, Nancy Mace, was seen in tears Tuesday after a meeting with some of Epstein's victims. Trump grew irritated Thursday when he was asked about the women's appeal to him.
title: Dozens of Jeffrey Epstein's Victims Call for Release of Epstein Files

author: Inside Edition
description: James Farthing won a $167 million Powerball prize last April. It was the largest in Kentucky state history. Farthing planned to share the vast sum with his mother. Two days after his win, the 50-year-old flew to Saint Pete Beach, Florida, and found himself in a headlock during a brawl with a guest at his hotel. Farthing made a run for it before police tased and handcuffed him. Now, the mega millionaire is facing charges of battery of a law enforcement officer and resisting an officer.
title: $167 Million Lottery Winner Charged After Florida Brawl

author: Inside Edition
description: A wedding crasher snatched a gift box filled with money and ran away. Newlyweds Nadeen and George Farahat say up until the theft, it had been a dream wedding day. The newlyweds say the gift box contained more than $80,000. Surveillance video shows a driver in an SUV Mercedes waiting in the alley then opening the passenger door and the thief jumping in. Police released images of the wedding crasher in hopes someone will recognize him.
title: Wedding Crasher Steals Gift Box With $80K, Newlyweds Say

author: Inside Edition
description: A snake tried to make a home in someone's shed, but the terrified homeowners were quick to call the Miami-Dade Fire Department, which dispatched its Venom One Unit. Captain Rusty Shaw says he never knows what to expect when he arrives at a call, but this seven-foot long Burmese python was fairly easy to handle. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Miami's Venom One Unit Captures 7-Foot Burmese Python From Homeowner's Shed

author: Inside Edition
description: Kids and parents alike were very confused to see cops arrest the one and only Chuck E. Cheese at his own establishment, but police in Tallahassee, Florida say they were really after the guy wearing the costume. Officials say Jermel Jones, 41, used a stolen credit card to make more than $100 in purchases. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Cops Arrest Man in Chuck E. Cheese Costume for Alleged Credit Card Fraud

author: Inside Edition
description: Stuffed robotic rabbits are supposed to attract predators, specifically the Burmese python, which officials say is wreaking havoc on the Florida Everglades.
title: Robot Bunnies Fight Pythons #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Elizabeth Banks is set to play Read in the new drama series for prime TV.
title: What Does Karen Read Think About Upcoming Series on Her Murder Trials?
